   "source": [
    "# TRIPPLE 7 MOVIE EMPIRE REVIEW"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Table of Content"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.Overview\n",
    "### 2.Data Loading and Exploration\n",
    "### 3.Data Cleaning and Preparation\n",
    "### 4.Business Analysis, Key Findings, and Recommendations\n",
    "### 5.Conclusion"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 1. OVERVIEW"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Tripple 7 movie empire is a start up company that wants to compete in the movie industry.  This analysis will help to give a general overview of the industry, to ensure the stakeholders understand how the industry works and what to expect of it, which will be ideal for decison making."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1.1 Business Problem"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Tripple Seven plans to launch a new movie studio but lacks experience in the film industry. The company does not know which types of movies perform best at the box office or what factors contribute to a film’s financial success.\n",
    "\n",
    "Without data-driven insights, investing in movie production could lead to poor financial outcomes. To reduce this risk, the company needs to understand how factors such as movie genre, release timing, and audience engagement affect revenue and profitability.\n",
    "\n",
    "This project aims to analyze historical movie data to identify successful patterns and provide clear recommendations that will help Tripple Seven make informed decisions on the types of films to produce.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1.2 Business Understanding"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Tripple 7 movie empire is a multi-billion dollar industry that has been growing rapidly in recent years due to various factors that have ensured a steady rise from the analog to digital eras.\n",
    "\n",
    "We've witnessed improvements in distribution, quality, genres, acting, among other things.\n",
    "\n",
    "One of the major factors has been the internet, which today is easily accessible to majority of the population worldwide. This has lead to the introduction of various streaming platforms, making it easy for viewers to download any type of movies they want to watch. Hence we have migrated from eras where we had to use compact disks(CD's/DVD's) which needed a physical store to buy them, to now using streaming platforms at the comfort of your home without needing to go out and get access to a particular movie, as long as you have internet access.\n",
    "\n",
    "Other factors have also majorly contributed to its growth, ie,\n",
    "\n",
    "- The use of various visual effects like CGI,VFX ensuring the movie is of high quality.\n",
    "- Large investments to ensure the logistics in a movie are met and the movie is finished and distributed on time.\n",
    "- Changing audience preferences ie genre preferences and cultural diversity has lead to content that caters to various audience.\n",
    "- Consumer spending due to strong economy can lead to high box office revenues.\n",
    "- Production and creative factors ie, script quality, acting skills, marketing and promotions can generate great revenues.\n",
    "\n",
    "However, all industries have their own risks that can impact various aspects in production like piracy, economic downturns, budget overruns, changing audience preferences, weather-related risks, casts illness/injury, poor box-office run, among other things.Therefore it is necessary to try and mitigate all/most of these risks during the planning and production periods. One of the main ways to reduce risks is by factoring data analysis to know the current trends and target audience."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 1.3 Objective"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. To determine the movie genres that are the most profitable.\n",
    "2. To determine the best time to release a movie for maximum returns.\n",
    "3. To determine whether higher-rated movies generate more revenue."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1.4 Business Questions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. Which movie genres are the most profitable?\n",
    "2. When is the best time to release a movie for maximum returns?\n",
    "3. Do higher-rated movies generate more revenue?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1.5 Dataset  Dictonary"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This dataset contains the following variables:\n",
    "● **Unnamed**: 0: Index column created during data export (not meaningful for analysis).\n",
    "\n",
    "● **genre_ids**: List of genre IDs associated with the movie.\n",
    "\n",
    "● **id_x**: Movie ID from the first dataset (e.g., TMDB dataset).\n",
    "\n",
    "● **original_language**: Original language in which the movie was produced (e.g., en).\n",
    "\n",
    "● **original_title**: Original title of the movie.\n",
    "\n",
    "● **popularity**: Popularity score based on user engagement and activity.\n",
    "\n",
    "● **release_date_x**: Movie release date from the first dataset (format: YYYY-MM-DD).\n",
    "\n",
    "● **title**: Movie title (standardized version).\n",
    "\n",
    "● **vote_average**: Average user rating (scale of 0–10).\n",
    "\n",
    "● **vote_count**: Total number of user votes received.\n",
    "\n",
    "● **id_y**: Movie ID from the second dataset after merging.\n",
    "\n",
    "● **release_date_y**: Movie release date from the second dataset (text format, e.g., Mar 26, 2010).\n",
    "\n",
    "● **movie**: Movie title from the second dataset.\n",
    "\n",
    "● **production_budget**: Total budget used to produce the movie (in USD, stored as a string with $).\n",
    "\n",
    "● **domestic_gross**: Revenue generated within the domestic market (USD).\n",
    "\n",
    "● **worldwide_gross**: Total global revenue generated by the movie (USD)."
   ]
  },
  {
