   "source": [
    "### 4.2.1 Key Finding"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e19082a7-5732-4672-aa31-6353d2fc5df7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Based on the analysis, genres such as Action, Adventure, and Animation show strong average profits across multiple films, making them reliable drivers of revenue."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4a65c2d6-7d0a-40d3-b5e1-18c1119fd03a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.2.2 Business Reommendation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f8ac2241-dde5-4f6d-a963-8195a0436aab",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Focus investment and production decisions on genres with consistently high profitability and sufficient movie volume.\n",
    "Prioritize Action, Adenture and Animation for future projects, marketing, and partnerships.At the same time, be cautious with genres that show lower or highly variable average profits, as they may carry greater financial risk unless supported by strong storytelling, star power, or lower production budgets."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f45d22eb-6bba-405d-9820-c61cdd98134b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4.2 Business Question 2: best time to release a movie for maximum returns"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7be7ded1-349b-444e-9a5a-7792853cdea9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### NOTE: mportance of Movie Count per Release Period:\n",
    "\n",
    "In this analysis, some months have significantly fewer movie releases than others, which can distort the average profit. For example, a single highly successful film released in a low-volume month could make that month appear more profitable than it actually is.\n",
    "\n",
    "To address this, we filtered for months, ensuring that the results reflect consistent performance rather than being driven by outliers. This makes the comparison of release timing more reliable and helps identify genuinely strong periods (such as peak months) for maximizing returns.\n"
   ]
