   "source": [
    "## 4.2.1 Key Findings"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "73611b26-9947-43d5-a192-188cd98751cd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "From our data Release timing also plays a significant role in profitability, with movies launched during summer (May–July) and holiday seasons (November–December) achieving the best financial results."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e3a038a3-01dd-4161-ba5a-4596626d8e80",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.2.2 Recommendations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ff61abf1-550d-4ce5-9e86-642cbe60e0c9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Based on these findings, it is recommended to prioritize production and investment in high-performing genres, schedule major releases during peak months to maximize returns, and carefully manage budgets for less consistent genres. Leveraging historical data and monitoring trends over time will help guide strategic decisions, minimize financial risk, and ensure that future releases achieve sustainable profitability."
   ]
  },
